headline: Jacobs Wins Key Low Carbon Projects With Shares Below Analyst Targets
summary: Jacobs Solutions (NYSE:J) has been selected to lead upgrades at the San Jose Santa Clara Regional Wastewater Facility in California. The company has also been chosen to support the Sizewell C nuclear power station project in the UK. Both contracts focus on large scale infrastructure and low carbon energy and water treatment work. For you as an investor, these new contracts sit at the core of what NYSE:J does: complex engineering, consulting, and project delivery across infrastructure,...
